2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 49
BY SENATOR CONNICK
A RESOLUTION
To commend and congratulate Melissa Adams on the occasion of her retirement from
Ochsner Medical Center - West Bank and to recognize her many accomplishments
throughout her career.
WHEREAS, after fifty-two years of dedicated service to the healthcare profession,
Melissa Adams is celebrating the occasion of her retirement; and
WHEREAS, Melissa has been a steadfast advocate for patients, a trusted leader for
nurses, a guiding force for the organization, and most importantly, a friend to everyone she
encounters; and
WHEREAS, her career has been nothing short of extraordinary; and
WHEREAS, while there is hardly a department at Ochsner Medical Center - West
Bank that she has not touched, it was the collaborative and team-focused environment of the
operating room where she found her true calling; and
WHEREAS, she started her career as a staff nurse in the operating room before being
promoted to director of surgical services, which included OR, PACU, anesthesia, endoscopy,
same-day surgery, and the sterile processing department; and
WHEREAS, when promoted to assistant vice president, Melissa assumed
responsibilities for the emergency department and critical care before becoming chief
nursing officer in 2010; and
WHEREAS, Melissa was instrumental in developing Senate Bill No. 136 of the 2022
Regular Session to address workplace violence in healthcare settings; and
WHEREAS, her career reflects an unwavering commitment to excellence,
compassion, and the advancement of nursing practice; and
WHEREAS, as chief nursing officer, Melissa shaped clinical care, mentored
hundreds of nurses, and led with integrity, vision, and heart; and
